{{Infobox Organization |name = Lake County Forest Preserves |image = |formation = 1958 |type = [[Governmental organization]] |purpose = Preservation, restoration, education and recreation (of open space in Lake County, IL) |headquarters = Libertyville, IL |coords = |region_served = Lake County, IL |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = Lake County Board |website = [http://www.lcfpd.org/index.cfm www.lcfpd.org] }}
'''Lake County Forest Preserves''' (also called Lake County Forest Preserve District, or LCFPD) is a governmental organization that purchases land and oversees the use of public open space in [[Lake County, Illinois]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Lake County|url=http://www.lcfpd.org/about/index.cfm?fuseaction=about.index|publisher=Lake County|accessdate=5 January 2014}}</ref> It is a member of [[Chicago Wilderness]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chicago Wilderness members|url=http://www.chicagowilderness.org/who-we-are/our-members/|publisher=Chicago Wilderness|accessdate=5 January 2014}}</ref>
The board of directors is also the board of Lake County. The directors are voted into office, and represent their respective districts in Lake County.
